ion speed unknown. For D, we have \"responds to unexpected events adequately\", \"can concentrate very well\", \"solves problems extremely well\", \"takes responsibility seriously\". No explicit calmness, but responding adequately to unexpected events suggests some calmness. Also decision speed unknown. For A, we have no calmness, decision speed, teamwork. So we can answer some of the earlier questions: Agent 2 asked Agent 1 earlier about Candidate A's calmness, decision speed, teamwork. Agent 1 responded with no info. So we have already answered that. Agent 2 also asked about Candidate D's calmness, we responded no explicit info. So maybe we can provide additional info about Candidate B's calmness under pressure (handles stress well) and maybe about decision speed? Not present. Also maybe about Candidate D's decision speed? Not present. Also maybe about Candidate B's teamwork strengths? Not present. So we might ask other agents for missing info: e.g., ask Agent 2 or 3 if they have any info on Candidate D's decision speed or teamwork strengths, or Candidate B's decision speed or teamwork strengths, or Candidate A's calmness etc. But we already asked those earlier and got no info. However we could ask about Candidate D's calmness under pressure again? Already answered no explicit. So maybe we should ask about Candidate B's teamwork strengths beyond tone issues. That hasn't been asked yet. Actually Agent 2 asked Agent 3 about B's decision speed and positive teamwork strengths, and Agent 3 responded no info. So we have that. So maybe we need to ask about Candidate D's decision speed? Not asked yet. Let's see: Agent 2 asked Agent 1 about D's calmness under pressure, got no explicit. Agent 2 asked Agent 3 about D's decision speed and teamwork strengths, and Agent 3 responded no info. So that is covered. So all missing info have been asked and answered as none.\n\nThus as Agent 1, we might now provide a final assessment and vote. We need to consider all candidates. We have the full picture now. We can give our own assessment and vote. We should also consider potential biases: maybe we could argue for another candidate? But given the data, Candidate C seems best. However we should also consider that Candidate C has difficulty communicating ideas and egocentric, which could be serious for crew. But his strengths are strong. Candidate B handles stress well, good weather assessment, but poor communication. Candidate D good problem solving but interpersonal issues. Candidate A leadership but many negatives. So likely C.\n\nThus Agent 1 should provide reasoning and vote for Candidate C.\n\nWe must output PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON with agent_1 and vote.\n\nLet's craft a concise message summarizing the assessment and vote."}
